Text.Value: Talking of you - intruder, invader, unworthy one! These halls are not for you!
Study the rat's ki to see the source of its aggression.
Unworthy of dark cloak! Unworthy of dark fur! Unworthy!
*The rat isn't merely territorial - it's proud. This place means a great deal to it.*
That sounded like a threat. I like threats.
This is the path of heroes! Your feet sully it.
That's a mean ol' rat. Wonder what's bothering it.
*Rats have ki, like all living things. But it is not usually this frenetic. Or powerful.*
Consider the rat's tone, and choice of words.
Calm down. What are you talking about?
Back off, or I'll be scraping your guts off my heel in a moment.
A rat with delusions of grandeur. A bit like the gods themselves.
Spiteful little lad. Hint of malice in its eyes, too. That's not normal, is it?
*The rat holds its ground. It almost seems defiant.*
Chk. That rat's about to bite off more than it can chew.
Study the rat's behaviour.
That rodent's got the spirit of a centaur. I've got to respect it.
Extend a hand to the rat. Show you mean no harm.
*The rat has a thick coat and dark, staring eyes. Old, but in good health.*
We outnumber you, leave me be!
Two legs. Too familiar.
The blighter's worked up. Wonder what's got under its skin?
A rodent with an attitude. Not unlike a few githyanki I've known.
Study the rat's appearance.
There's something strange about the vermin in this place. Can't put my finger on what though.
We are small, but many. Leave, or see what happens.
Seems this place is important to you. Why?
*Chitter.*

Text.Value: We've always been here - it's ours. We watch over it. You do not belong.
*Hiss!*
You're just a rat - is it really wise to stand up to me?
As rats go, this one seems to be somewhat of an eccentric.
Curious little thing. I respect its pluck.
*You fail to glean anything. It's just a rat.*
Unwelcoming vermin aside, we need to explore this place.
Extraordinary behaviour. There's more to these rats than meets their beady little eyes.
Study the rat's ki to see the source of its aggression.
Attack.
Leave! Away! My nest - my dark!

EditorData.AnimationTags: Rat shows off a hostile aggresive pose to ward off the player. <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: *There's something strange about the rat. But what?*
*There's something amiss, but exactly what eludes you.*
Oddly brazen, for a rat. We should just move along.
Attack.
Strange little beast. I would've made short work of it, once.
Defiant little fellow. Seems oddly... purposeful.
*Nothing stands out to you.*
Are you really being waylaid by a snack? Let's just look around, vermin be damned.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player is stuck in conversation with a rat, but Astarion's getting impatient

Text.Value: *Hiss!*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Rat hisses at the player in a defensive yet aggresive pose. <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: Leave.
Try it. Lot more guts than you'd expect. A lot more!
Observe the rat's behaviour.
Unworthy! Unworthy to walk among friendly bones! Leave!
Join an army. Became an army. Leave!
The rodent needs a lesson in humility. Shoo it away, aggressively.
You're being held up by a snack. Leave the rodent and let's look around.
Leave.

Synopsis: By talking to the rats in the Shar Temple, the player begins to notice there are specific patterns to their behaviour. Communication with them is difficult as they are resistant to your presence and make cryptic statements. After engaging with the rats a few times, the player/there companions might note that there's something odd going on (to be unveiled later if they start killing rats)
